        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 22 at 4:53AM MDT by NWS Missoula MT</headline>
        <description>At 452 AM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking an intense snow shower near
Warm Springs, or near Anaconda, moving east at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Visibility one-half mile or less and winds in excess of 30
mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Low visibility could result in dangerous driving
conditions. Gusty winds could blow around unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Nissler, Crackerville, Dewey, Fishtrap, Walkerville, Warm Springs,
Butte, Anaconda, Galen, Racetrack, Gregson Hot Springs, Divide, Deer
Lodge, Lost Creek, Opportunity, Silver Bow, West Valley, Ramsay,
Janney, and Newcomb.

This includes Interstate 90 between mile markers 186 and 231.
</description>
        <instruction>This storm may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional information
and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
